Create a clean, minimalist scientific illustration on a pure white background in landscape format (16:9, but square also acceptable).

The composition should show a circular diagram representing a self-reinforcing news cycle.

On the left side of the circle:

The Wikipedia globe logo (black and white puzzle globe style, but not overly detailed)

A clear label underneath: “Wikipedia”

On the right side of the circle:

Stylized traditional media icons (stack of newspapers, a magazine, and a simple press/news symbol)

Label underneath: “Media”

Between them, form a circular loop with two bold curved arrows:

Arrow from Wikipedia → Media labeled:
“Wikipedia references media”

Arrow from Media → Wikipedia labeled:
“Journalists source information from Wikipedia”

The arrows should visually form a closed circle to emphasize self-referencing.

Style requirements:

Clean vector style

Flat design

No gradients

Black, gray, and muted blue color palette

Clear readable sans-serif typography

Balanced, symmetric layout

Professional academic look

No shadows, no 3D effects

High resolution

The overall impression should subtly convey a narrowed-down, slightly polemic depiction of a circular self-reinforcing information loop.
